sub_title: EALD Teacher, Library & Sustainability Coordinator at SALTO International School RISE
summary:
I am an Australian teacher, graduated from a Master of Teaching in 2017. I have moved to the Netherlands to connect with my mum's Dutch relatives, the country my grandparents left after WWII, and to learn the Dutch language. 

I am passionate about language and literature, and have confidence through learning both we can have a stronger understanding of the multicultural world we all share. I love authors' depiction of the past, present, and futures of different cultures. I seek to learn all I can about our history as a human race, believing we need to reflect on our mistakes and triumphs in order to move forward. I endeavour to make choices for the sustainability of our planet. In my classrooms, I strive to create open and questioning learning environments, with a curiosity and growing responsibility for the world around them.  

I try to read as many novels as I can throughout the year, mostly fiction and anything by Stephen King that isn't horror. I love watching films in the cinema. Although I come from rural South Australia, I cannot surf or play football. I do enjoy dragon boat paddling and hope to find a Dutch team. I love exploring the Dutch countryside with my cousins and have embraced the Dutch cycling culture: ‘Ik ben niet gemaakt van suiker.’
